.Dd August 14, 2012
.Dt STI 8
.Os
.Sh NAME
.Nm sti
.Nd Simulate Terminal Input: send characters to a tty device
.Sh SYNOPSIS
.Nm
.Ar tty
.Op Ar string ...
.Sh DESCRIPTION
.Nm
connects to the specified
.Ar tty
and uses the
.Dv TIOCSTI
.Xr ioctl 2
to enter text as if it were typed in.
This
.Xr ioctl 2
is limited to the superuser.
.Pp
.Nm
will send the provided
.Ar string
if any; otherwise it sends the standard input.
The
.Ar string
is interpreted using
.Xr unvis 3 .
.Sh SEE ALSO
.Xr ioctl 2 ,
.Xr unvis 3
.Sh HISTORY
The
.Nm
command first appeared in
.Nx 4.0 .
.Sh AUTHORS
The
.Nm
command was written by
